ational-football-teams.com/player/12929/Zesh_Rehman.html|publisher=National Football Teams|accessdate=22 May 2015}}</ref>\n|[[Thai Premier League]]\n|30||1||||||||||5{{efn|Appearances in [[AFC Cup]] and [[AFC Champions League]]|name=AFCL}}||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||35||1\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[Kitchee S.C.|Kitchee]]\n|[[2011\u201312 Kitchee SC season|2011\u201312]]<ref name=\"SW\"/>\n|[[Hong Kong First Division League|First Division League]]\n|9||0||4||1||3||0||7{{efn|Appearances in [[AFC Cup]]|name=AFC}}||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||23||2\n|-\n|[[2012\u201313 Kitchee SC season|2012\u201313]]<ref name=\"SW\"/>\n|First Division League\n|15||0||4||0||0||0||9{{efn|Appearances in [[AFC Cup]]|name=AFC}}||0||2{{efn|Appearances in [[Hong Kong Senior Shield]]|name=SS}}||0||30||0\n|-\n|[[2013\u201314 Kitchee SC season|2013\u201314]]<ref name=\"SW\"/>\n|First Division League\n|6||0||4||0||0||0||0||0||1{{efn|Appearances in [[Hong Kong Senior Shield]]|name=SS}}||0||11||0\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!30!!0!!12!!0!!3!!0!!16!!1!!3!!0!!64!!1\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[Pahang FA]]\n|[[2014 Pahang FA season|2014]]<ref name=\"SW\"/>\n|[[Malaysia Super League]]\n| 21||1||10||3||7||1||0||0||0||0||38||5\n|-\n|[[2015 Pahang FA season|2015]]<ref name=\"SW\"/>\n|Malaysia Super League\n|21||6||10||1||6||1||8{{efn|Appearances in [[AFC Cup]]|name=AFC}}||0||0||0||45||8\n|-\n|[[2016 Pahang FA season|2016]]<ref name=\"SW\"/>\n|Malaysia Super League\n|10||0||||||1||0||||||||||11||0\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!52!!8!!20!!4!!14!!2!!8!!0!!0!!0!!94!!13\n|-\n|[[Gillingham FC|Gillingham]]\n|2017\n|League One||10||1||0||0||0||0||0||0||0||0||10||1\n|-\n|[[Southern District FC|Southern]]\n|2017-18\n|[[Hong Kong Premier League]]||32||0||7||0||5||0||1||0||0||0||45||0\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|Career total\n!311!!13!!44!!4!!35!!3!!30!!1!!8!!0!!441!!22\n|}\n{{notelist}}\n\n===International===\n{{updated|12 September 2018.}}<ref name=\"Zesh Rehman\">{{NFT player|id=12929|name=Zesh Rehman|accessdate = 8 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n! National team !! Year !! Apps !! Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"8\"|[[Pakistan national football team|Pakistan]]\n| 2005 || 4 || 0\n|-\n| 2006 || 2 || 0\n|-\n| 2007 || 2 || 0\n|-\n| 2010 || 1 || 0\n|-\n| 2011 || 3 || 0\n|-\n| 2012 || 1 || 0\n|-\n| 2013 || 5 || 1\n|-\n| 2018 || 5 || 0\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" | Total !! 23 !! 1\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[British Asians in association football]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Zesh Rehman}}\n*[http://www.zeshrehman.com/ Official website of Zesh Rehman]\n* {{twitter|Zesh_Rehman}}\n* {{instagram|zesh_rehman}}\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n*{{FIFA player|288418}}\n\n{{Pakistan squad 2018 SAFF Championship}}\n{{Southern District FC squad}}\n{{2011\u201312 Hong Kong Top Footballer}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rehman, Zesh}}\n[[Category:1983 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Birmingham, West Midlands]]\n[[Category:English people of Pakistani descent]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:English expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:England youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Pakistani expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Pakistani footballers]]\n[[Category:Pakistan international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Fulham F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Brighton & Hove Albion F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Norwich City F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Queens Park Rangers F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Blackpool F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Bradford City A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Muangthong United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Kitchee SC players]]\n[[Category:Pahang FA players]]\n[[Category:Southern District FC players]]\n[[Category:Premier League players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:Hong Kong Premier League players]]\n[[Category:Thai League 1 players]]\n[[Category:Malaysia Super League players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Thailand]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Hong Kong]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Malaysia]]\n[[Category:Citizens of Pakistan through descent]]\n[[Category:British sportspeople of Pakistani descent]]\n", "name_user": "GiantSnowman", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eFulham:clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zesh_Rehman"}
{"title_page": "Ben Judge", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=April 2018}}\n{{Infobox snooker player\n|name         = Ben Judge\n|image        = \n|caption      = \n|birth_date   = {{birth date and age|1983|9|18|df=y}}\n|birth_place   = [[Perth, Western Australia]], [[Australia]]\n| Sport country = {{AUS}}\n| Nickname  =\n| Professional = 2012/2013\n| High ranking = 83 <small>(July 2012)</small><ref>{{cite web|title=World Rankings after 2012 Wuxi Classic|url=http://www.worldsnooker.com/staticFiles/ee/b5/0,,13165~177646,00.pdf|work=worldsnooker.com|publisher=[[World Professional Billiards and Snooker Association]]|format=PDF|accessdate=28 May 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928183819/http://www.worldsnooker.com/staticFiles/ee/b5/0%2C%2C13165~177646%2C00.pdf|archivedate=28 September 2013|df=}}</ref>\n| Prize money  = [[Pound sterling|\u00a3]]2,053\n| High break   = \n| Century break = \n| Best finish  = Last 80 <small>([[2012 Shanghai Masters]])</small>\n| Ranking wins = \n| Minor wins =\n| World champ  = \n}}\n'''Ben Judge''' (born  18 September 1983) is a former [[Australian people|Australian]] professional snooker player, from [[Perth, Western Australia|Perth]].<ref name=\"ws\"/>\n\n==Snooker career==\nJudge, as an amateur played in a pre-qualifying match for the [[2000 World Snooker Championship]]  losing 5\u20133 to [[Atthasit Mahitthi]].<ref name=\"cuetracker9900\">{{cite web|title=Ben Judge - Season 1999/2000|url=http://www.cuetracker.net/pages/players.php?ID=840&season=1999/2000|publisher=CueTracker - Snooker Database|accessdate=18 August 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140819083455/http://www.cuetracker.net/pages/players.php?ID=840&season=1999%2F2000|archivedate=19 August 2014|df=}}</ref> In 2011, Judge attempted the qualify for the [[World Snooker Tour]] via the [[World Snooker Q School|Q School]] but was unsuccessful.<ref name=\"psb\">{{cite web|title=Ben Judge|url=http://www.prosnookerblog.com/players/i-l/ben-judge/|publisher=Pro Snooker Blog|accessdate=18 August 2014}}</ref> A year later, Judge won a place on the professional tour for the [[2012\u201313 snooker season|2012\u201313]] and [[2013\u201314 snooker season|2013\u201314]] seasons after winning the 2012 Oceania Championship, 6\u20132 over [[James Mifsud]].<ref name=\"psb\"/><ref name=\"ws\">{{cite web |title=Ben Judge |url=http://www.worldsnooker.com/page/PlayersAlphabeticalArticle/0,,13165~2806361,00.html |publisher=World Snooker |accessdate=18 August 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140819082715/http://www.worldsnooker.com/page/PlayersAlphabeticalArticle/0%2C%2C13165~2806361%2C00.html |archivedate=19 August 2014 |df= }}</ref> He had two wins, one against [[Sam Baird]] in the Last 96 stage of the [[2012 Shanghai Masters]] qualifiers and the other against [[Alan McManus]] in the [[European Tour 2012/2013 \u2013 Event 2|2012 Gdynia Open]] Last 128 stage.<ref name=\"psb\"/> He last played in the qualifiers for the [[2013 German Masters]] in November 2012<ref name=\"psb\"/> and resigned from the tour in November 2013.<ref name=\"resigned\">{{cite web|title=Updated World Rankings|url=http://www.worldsnooker.com/page/NewsArticles/0,,13165~3523567,00.html|publisher=[[World Professional Billiards and Snooker Association]]|work=worldsnooker.com|accessdate=14 August 2014|date=4 November 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131107054615/http://www.worldsnooker.com/page/NewsArticles/0%2C%2C13165~3523567%2C00.html|archivedate=7 November 2013|df=}}</ref>\n\nJudge won two group matches at the [[2014 Six-red World Championship]] to qualify for the last 32, where [[Stephen Maguire]] beat him 6\u20134.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://snooker.org/res/index.asp?season=2014&player=537 | title=Ben Judge 2014/2015 | publisher=Snooker.org | accessdate=10 May 2015}}</ref> He was eliminated in the group stage a [[2015 Six-red World Championship|year later]] and was defeated in the wildcard of the [[2015 Australian Goldfields Open]] by [[Matthew Selt]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.snooker.org/res/index.asp?season=2015&player=537 | title=Ben Judge 2015/2016 | publisher=Snooker.org | accessdate=26 September 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Performance and rankings timeline==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"  style=\"font-size:85%;\"\n|- style=\"background:#efefef;\"\n! '''Tournament'''\n! [[1999\u201300 snooker season|1999/<br/>00]]\n! [[2012\u201313 snooker season|2012/<br/>13]] \n! [[2014\u201315 snooker season|2014/<br/>15]]\n|-\n|style=\"background:#EFEFEF;\"| [[Snooker world rankings|Ranking]]<ref name=\"Ranking history\">{{cite web|title=Ranking History|url=http://www.snooker.org/rnk/history.asp|publisher=Snooker.org|accessdate=6 February 2011}}</ref><ref group=\"nb\">It shows the ranking at the beginning of the season.</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref group=\"nb\" name=\"AMA\">He was an amateur.</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref group=\"nb\" name=\"UR\">New players don't have a ranking.</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref group=\"nb\" name=\"AMA\"/>\n|-\n| colspan=\"9\" | '''Ranking Tournaments'''\n|-\n|style=\"background:#EFEFEF;\"| [[Wuxi Classic]]\n| align=\"center\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\"| NH\n| align=\"center\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\"| LQ\n| align=\"center\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\"| A\n|-\n|style=\"background:#EFEFEF;\"| [[Australian Goldfields Open]]\n| align=\"center\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\"| NH\n| align=\"center\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\"| LQ\n| align=\"center\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\"| A\n|-\n|style=\"background:#EFEFEF;\"| [[Shanghai Masters (snooker)|Shanghai Masters]]\n| align=\"center\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\"| NH\n| align=\"center\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\"| LQ\n| align=\"center\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\"| A\n|-\n|style=\"background:#EFEFEF;\"| [[International Championship]]\n| align=\"center\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\"| NH\n| align=\"center\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\"| LQ\n| align=\"center\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\"| A\n|-\n|style=\"background:#EFEFEF;\"| [[UK Championship (snooker)|UK Championship]]\n| align=\"center\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\"| A\n| align=\"center\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\"| LQ\n| align=\"center\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\"| A\n|-\n|style=\"background:#EFEFEF;\"| [[German Masters]]\n| align=\"center\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\"| NH\n| align=\"center\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\"| LQ\n| align=\"center\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\"| A\n|-\n|style=\"background:#EFEFEF;\"| [[Players Championship Grand Final|Players Tour Championship Finals]]\n| align=\"center\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\"| NH\n| align=\"center\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\"| DNQ\n| align=\"center\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\"| A\n|-\n|style=\"background:#EFEFEF;\"| [[World Snooker Championship|World Championship]]\n| align=\"center\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\"| LQ\n| align=\"center\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\"| A\n| align=\"center\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\"| A\n|-\n|colspan=\"9\" | '''Variant Format Tournaments'''\n|-\n|style=\"background:#EFEFEF;\" | [[Six-red World Championship]]\n| align=\"center\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\"| NH\n| align=\"center\" style=\"background:#afeeee;\"|[[2012 Six-red World Championship|RR]]\n| align=\"center\" style=\"background:#afeeee;\"|[[2014 Six-red World Championship|1R]]\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:78%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#efefef\"\n! colspan=\"6\"|Performance Table Legend\n|-\n| align=\"center\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\" width=\"30\"|LQ\n| lost in the qualifying draw\n| align=\"center\" style=\"background:#afeeee;\"|#R\n| lost in the early rounds of the tournament<br />(WR = Wildcard round, RR = Round robin)\n| align=\"center\" style=\"background:#ffebcd;\"|QF\n| lost in the quarter-finals\n|-\n| align=\"center\" style=\"background:yellow;\"|SF\n| lost in the semi-finals\n| align=\"center\" style=\"background:#D8BFD8;\"|F\n| lost in the final\n| align=\"center\" style=\"background:#00ff00;\"|'''W'''\n| won the tournament\n|-\n| align=\"center\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\" width=\"30\"|DNQ\n| did not qualify for the tournament\n| align=\"center\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\" width=\"30\"|A\n| did not participate in the tournament\n| align=\"center\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\" width=\"30\"|WD\n| withdrew from the tournament\n|}\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%\"\n|-\n|  style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\" colspan=\"4\"|NH / Not Held || means an event was not held.\n|-\n|  style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\" colspan=\"4\"|NR / Non-Ranking Event || means an event is/was no longer a ranking event.\n|-\n|  style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\" colspan=\"4\"|R / Ranking Event || means an event is/was a ranking event.\n|-\n|  style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\" colspan=\"4\"|MR / Minor-Ranking Event || means an event is/was a minor-ranking event.\n|}\n{{reflist|group=nb}}\n\n==Notes==\n:A. {{note|years}} Judge resigned from the tour in November 2013, halfway through the [[2013\u201314 snooker season|2013\u201314 season]].<ref name=\"resigned\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20140819082715/http://www.worldsnooker.com/page/PlayersAlphabeticalArticle/0%2C%2C13165~2806361%2C00.html Profile on worldsnooker.com]\n* \n* [http://www.prosnookerblog.com/players/i-l/ben-judge/ Profile on Pro Snooker Blog]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Judge, Ben}}\n[[Category:Australian snooker players]]\n[[Category:Sportsmen from Western Australia]]\n[[Category:1983 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Perth, Western Australia]]\n\n\n{{snooker-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=April 2018}}\n{{Infobox snooker player\n|name         = Ben Judge\n|image        = \n|caption      = \n|birth_date   = {{birth date and age|1983|9|18|df=y}}\n|birth_place   = [[Perth, Western Australia]], [[Australia]]\n| Sport country = {{AUS}}\n| Nickname  =\n| Professional = 2012/2013\n| High ranking = 83 <small>(July 2012)</small><ref>{{cite web|title=World Rankings after 2012 Wuxi Classic|url=http://www.worldsnooker.com/staticFiles/ee/b5/0,,13165~177646,00.pdf|work=worldsnooker.com|publisher=[[World Professional Billiards and Snooker Association]]|format=PDF|accessdate=28 May 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928183819/http://www.worldsnooker.com/staticFiles/ee/b5/0%2C%2C13165~177646%2C00.pdf|archivedate=28 September 2013|df=}}</ref>\n| Prize money  = [[Pound sterling|\u00a3]]2,053\n| High break   = \n| Century break = \n| Best finish  = Last 80 <small>([[2012 Shanghai Masters]])</small>\n| Ranking wins = \n| Minor wins =\n| World champ  = \n}}\n'''Ben Judge''' (born  18 September 1983) is a former [[Australian people|Australian]] professional snooker player, from [[Perth, Western Australia|Perth]].<ref name=\"ws\"/>\n\n==Snooker career==\nJudge, as an amateur played in a pre-qualifying match for the [[2000 World Snooker Championship]]  losing 5\u20133 to [[Atthasit Mahitthi]].<ref name=\"cuetracker9900\">{{cite web|title=Ben Judge - Season 1999/2000|url=http://www.cuetracker.net/pages/players.php?ID=840&season=1999/2000|publisher=CueTracker - Snooker Database|accessdate=18 August 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140819083455/http://www.cuetracker.net/pages/players.php?ID=840&season=1999%2F2000|archivedate=19 August 2014|df=}}</ref> In 2011, Judge attempted the qualify for the [[World Snooker Tour]] via the [[World Snooker Q School|Q School]] but was unsuccessful.<ref name=\"psb\">{{cite web|title=Ben Judge|url=http://www.prosnookerblog.com/players/i-l/ben-judge/|publisher=Pro Snooker Blog|accessdate=18 August 2014}}</ref> A year later, Judge won a place on the professional tour for the [[Snooker season 2012/2013|2012/2013]] and [[Snooker season 2013/2014|2013/2014]] seasons after winning the 2012 Oceania Championship, 6\u20132 over [[James Mifsud]].<ref name=\"psb\"/><ref name=\"ws\">{{cite web |title=Ben Judge |url=http://www.worldsnooker.com/page/PlayersAlphabeticalArticle/0,,13165~2806361,00.html |publisher=World Snooker |accessdate=18 August 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140819082715/http://www.worldsnooker.com/page/PlayersAlphabeticalArticle/0%2C%2C13165~2806361%2C00.html |archivedate=19 August 2014 |df= }}</ref> He had two wins, one against [[Sam Baird]] in the Last 96 stage of the [[2012 Shanghai Masters]] qualifiers and the other against [[Alan McManus]] in the [[European Tour 2012/2013 \u2013 Event 2|2012 Gdynia Open]] Last 128 stage.<ref name=\"psb\"/> He last played in the qualifiers for the [[2013 German Masters]] in November 2012<ref name=\"psb\"/> and resigned from the tour in November 2013.<ref name=\"resigned\">{{cite web|title=Updated World Rankings|url=http://www.worldsnooker.com/page/NewsArticles/0,,13165~3523567,00.html|publisher=[[World Professional Billiards and Snooker Association]]|work=worldsnooker.com|accessdate=14 August 2014|date=4 November 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131107054615/http://www.worldsnooker.com/page/NewsArticles/0%2C%2C13165~3523567%2C00.html|archivedate=7 November 2013|df=}}</ref>\n\nJudge won two group matches at the [[2014 Six-red World Championship]] to qualify for the last 32, where [[Stephen Maguire]] beat him 6\u20134.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://snooker.org/res/index.asp?season=2014&player=537 | title=Ben Judge 2014/2015 | publisher=Snooker.org | accessdate=10 May 2015}}</ref> He was eliminated in the group stage a [[2015 Six-red World Championship|year later]] and was defeated in the wildcard of the [[2015 Australian Goldfields Open]] by [[Matthew Selt]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.snooker.org/res/index.asp?season=2015&player=537 | title=Ben Judge 2015/2016 | publisher=Snooker.org | accessdate=26 September 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Performance and rankings timeline==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"  style=\"font-size:85%;\"\n|- styl